  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Salad Shop Kitchen Staff",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Kitchen Assistant / Food Prep Crew</strong></h3><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Perform stock-taking and place orders as needed to ensure sufficient inventory for daily operations</p></li><li><p>Prepare kitchen ingredients efficiently and consistently, following F&B best practices</p></li><li><p>Ensure all ingredient preparation complies with <strong>food hygiene</strong> and <strong>halal</strong> standards</p></li><li><p>Maintain overall <strong>cleanliness</strong> and organization of the kitchen in accordance with safety and hygiene regulations</p></li><li><p>Monitor and maintain <strong>freshness and quality</strong> of all ingredients</p></li><li><p>Assist in any <strong>ad-hoc duties</strong> as assigned by managers or supervisors</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>1 year of experience</strong> in the F&B industry</p></li><li><p><strong>Team player</strong> with a positive attitude</p></li><li><p>Willing to learn, with <strong>strong integrity</strong> and good work ethic</p></li><li><p>Able to comply with <strong>Food Hygiene & Halal regulations</strong></p></li></ul><p><strong>Working Hours & Benefits:</strong></p><ul><li><p>44-hour work week, <strong>5.5 days</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>Saturday afternoon and Sunday off</strong></p></li><li><p><strong>All public holidays off</strong> (no shifts required)</p></li></ul>",
